<item>
            <title>[FELIX-355] ConfigurationAdmin service is unregistered after it has been cleaned up</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-355</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ConfigurationManager as the BundleActivator of the Configuration Admin implementation shuts down and cleans up in the stop(BundleContext) method and leaves unregistration of the service to the framework. This causes potential issues in active environments, where the ConfigurationAdmin service may still be used albeit it has already been clean up.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ConfigurationManager.stop method should actually unregister the service before cleaning up.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
